messages.content: What are the two webUI extensions implemented by cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI?
The cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI custom node implements two webUI extensions created by hako-mikan: sd-webui-cd-tuner and sd-webui-negpip.
What is the primary function of the sd-webui-cd-tuner extension?
The primary function of the sd-webui-cd-tuner extension is to adjust color tones and writing amount, although it currently only implements certain features.
What functionality does the sd-webui-negpip extension provide?
The sd-webui-negpip extension provides the functionality to implement negative weights in prompts.
How should the start and end values be specified in the cd-tuner?
The start and end values in the cd-tuner should be specified in the range of 0 to 1000.
Is it necessary to specify the start and end values in steps?
No, start and end values in the cd-tuner do not need to be specified in step units, it is due to implementation reasons.
Who is the author of the cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI custom node?
The cd-tuner_negpip-ComfyUI custom node was implemented by hako-mikan.
